{"id":4610,"date":"2017-05-05T09:20:19","date_gmt":"2017-05-05T09:20:19","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/?p=4610"},"modified":"2019-02-22T21:17:15","modified_gmt":"2019-02-22T21:17:15","slug":"inspirational-addiction-recovery-quotes","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/inspirational-addiction-recovery-quotes\/","title":{"rendered":"Inspirational Addiction Recovery Quotes"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Sometimes the right words can lend us immediate and lasting strength. We\u2019ve gathered a collection of inspiring addiction recovery quotes to help those on the path to recovery.<br \/>\n<!--more--><\/p>\n<h2>May the Bridges I Burn Light the Way<\/h2>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-4613\" title=\"1st - Most Inspirational Recovery Quote - Pathways Real Life Recovery, Utah\" src=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/1-1.png\" alt=\"May the Bridges I Burn Light the Way\" width=\"600\" height=\"315\" srcset=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/1-1.png 1200w, https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/1-1-300x157.png 300w, https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/1-1-768x402.png 768w, https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/1-1-1024x536.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>People who recover from addiction have consciously resolved to leave some people and places in the rear-view mirror. It\u2019s OK\u2014necessary\u2014to disengage from people who aren\u2019t supporting\u00a0our recovery.<\/p>\n<p>Yet we need to examine those former paths of ours. They can teach us\u00a0to avoid similar situations\u2014to make better future decisions.<\/p>\n<h2>You Can\u2019t Change What\u2019s Going on Around You Until You Start Changing What\u2019s Going On Within You<\/h2>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-4617\" title=\"2nd - Most Inspirational Recovery Quote - Pathways Real Life Recovery, Utah\" src=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2-1.png\" alt=\"You Can\u2019t Change What\u2019s Going on Around You Until You Start Changing What\u2019s Going On Within You\" width=\"600\" height=\"315\" srcset=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2-1.png 1200w, https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2-1-300x157.png 300w, https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2-1-768x402.png 768w, https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2-1-1024x536.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>When things keep going wrong, it\u2019s hard to resist anger at other people. But recovery starts in wanting\u00a0major changes within the self. We want to get better.<\/p>\n<h2>You Have to Get Up Every Morning and Tell Yourself \u201cI Can Do This.\u201d<\/h2>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-4616\" title=\"3rd - Most Inspirational Recovery Quote - Pathways Real Life Recovery, Utah\" src=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/3.png\" alt=\"You Have to Get Up Every Morning and Tell Yourself \u201cI Can Do This.\u201d\" width=\"600\" height=\"315\" srcset=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/3.png 1200w, https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/3-300x157.png 300w, https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/3-768x402.png 768w, https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/3-1024x536.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>What\u2019s the language of that voice in our head? If it\u2019s \u201cIt can\u2019t work\u201d or \u201cI\u2019m going to fail at this\u201d then it\u2019s time to re-train the brain. Change your inner voice into your coach, drumming into you powerful self-belief, transforming your life\u2019s interactions.<\/p>\n<h2>At the Root of All Addiction is Pain<\/h2>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-4612\" title=\"4th - Most Inspirational Recovery Quote - Pathways Real Life Recovery, Utah\" src=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/6.png\" alt=\"At the Root of All Addiction is Pain\" width=\"600\" height=\"315\" srcset=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/6.png 1200w, https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/6-300x157.png 300w, https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/6-768x402.png 768w, https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/6-1024x536.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Shame and loneliness are\u00a0painful to human beings, and are the top triggers for relapse. In contrast, love, connection, and communication can heal. So we focus on\u00a0healing the shame, working on deep self-worth, accountability, and connections with others.<\/p>\n<h2>A Trigger is a Connection Between the Conscious Mind and a Buried Painful Memory<\/h2>\n<p>Effective treatment identifies our triggers and enables us to overcome them. Conscious knowledge of where that mental pain came from, and how it shapes our reactions, allows us to make our own decisions about how to respond.<\/p>\n<p>Imagine how we can change our lives if we could free ourselves from traps set up by the past, and take the lead our decisions.<\/p>\n<h2>It Won\u2019t Be Like This Forever<\/h2>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-4614\" title=\"5th - Most Inspirational Recovery Quote - Pathways Real Life Recovery, Utah\" src=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/5.png\" alt=\"A Trigger is a Connection Between the Conscious Mind and a Buried Painful Memory\" width=\"600\" height=\"315\" srcset=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/5.png 1200w, https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/5-300x157.png 300w, https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/5-768x402.png 768w, https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/5-1024x536.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Addiction makes a person feel hopeless and trapped. But heal the underlying cause that drives us to use, and yes: It is possible to end an addiction.<\/p>\n<p>Yes, a person can become entrenched in a cycle. It\u2019s not helpful to be shamed for a habitual behavior and state of mind which becomes a trap. But people can change their minds and behavior. To say one is doomed is an illusion.<\/p>\n<h2>One of the Hardest Things Was Learning I was Worth Recovery<\/h2>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-4615\" title=\"6th - Most Inspirational Recovery Quote - Pathways Real Life Recovery, Utah\" src=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/4.png\" alt=\"It Won\u2019t Be Like This Forever \" width=\"600\" height=\"315\" srcset=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/4.png 1200w, https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/4-300x157.png 300w, https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/4-768x402.png 768w, https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/4-1024x536.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Addiction leads to embarrassing actions that are out of character. Everyone is worth recovery. At Pathways, we know it&#8217;s\u00a0essentially about loving ourselves.\u00a0Sometimes it\u2019s the hardest thing to learn. Pathways can bring you to your real solution.<\/p>\n<h2>Sobriety Looks Good on You<\/h2>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-4611\" title=\"7th - Most Inspirational Recovery Quote - Pathways Real Life Recovery, Utah\" src=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/7.png\" alt=\"One of the Hardest Things Was Learning I was Worth Recovery\" width=\"600\" height=\"315\" srcset=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/7.png 1200w, https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/7-300x157.png 300w, https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/7-768x402.png 768w, https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/7-1024x536.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Dealing with our issues makes us admirable\u2014to ourselves and to others. We become the kind of folks others look up to.<\/p>\n<p>Our tailor-made, intensive outpatient program addresses any kind of destructive issues: marital, personal, disorders, pornography, and more. We break the cycle of guilt and shame, helping clients accept where they are in order to make life changes. We treat our clients with love, dignity, and respect.<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><a title=\"Download PDF - Most Inspirational Recovery Quote - Pathways Real Life Recovery, Utah\" href=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/pathwaysreallife.com-Inspirational-Addiction-Recovery-Quotes.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Download PDF<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Sometimes the right words can lend us immediate and lasting strength. We\u2019ve gathered a collection of inspiring addiction recovery quotes to help those on the path to recovery.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":3,"featured_media":4616,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[41,52],"tags":[],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v16.8 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/wordpress\/plugins\/seo\/ -->\n<title>Most Inspirational Recovery Quotes - Pathways Real Life Recovery, Utah<\/title>\n<meta name=\"description\" content=\"At Pathways Real Life Recovery, Utah. We\u2019ve gathered some of the most inspirational recovery quotes to help those on the path to recovery.\" \/>\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow, max-snippet:-1, max-image-preview:large, max-video-preview:-1\" \/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/inspirational-addiction-recovery-quotes\/\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:locale\" content=